headline: Don't Blame AI For Weaker Hiring: JPMorgan's Dimon
summary: Artificial intelligence won't dramatically affect unemployment in the near term, but companies are pulling back on hiring because they want to be more efficient, according to JPMorgan CEO Jamie Dimon.  "I don't think A.I. is going to dramatically reduce jobs, like, unbelievably next year," Dimon said in an interview that aired Sunday morning.

headline: Looking at the Narrative for JPMorgan After Analyst Upgrades and Rising Expense Pressures
summary: JPMorgan Chase's latest narrative update keeps its fair value estimate steady at about $328.09 per share, even as a slightly lower discount rate and largely unchanged revenue growth outlook underscore analysts' confidence in the bank's long term earnings power.
